notes:
Flanges should always be bolted to full flat faced flanges. Where full flat faced flanges are not used; proper spacers must be used to build-up 
the flange to a flat surface and prevent overstressing the flange. When existing equipment cannot be modified to produce full flat faced flange; 
Stub end Flange shall be used./To be used for Raw water Services only/To be used for Cooling Water Return (WCR); Cooling Water Supply (WCS); Desalinated Water (WDS); Water Vapor over phosphoric Acid (GPA) ; Process Condensate (CPP) ;Process Water (WPR); Cooling Water Return Closed loop (CWCR); Flocculant (FLT)

According to BCT valve specification. To be used only for Silica (SiO2) with > 70%-wt moisture (SiO1); H2SiF6 
5-45%-wt; with SiO2; traces of SIF4; HF (FSA1); SiF4 gas with HF traces (SiF1a); Waste gas (containing HF; 
SiF4;H2O; Air) (GW1a); Waste water without solids (WW1); Potassium hydroxide KOH (KOH).
